translated: Carlsten, Bengt Erik, Captain, read-court official, Vänersborg, born on December 21, 1886 in Nättraby, Blekinge County, son of dock supervisor Johan C. and Mina Sjögren. Married 1911 to Gärda KöMander. They have three children: Eric born in 1913, Olof born in 1919, and Anna born in 1921. He passed his Mog:ex. (examination for people with gymnasium education) in Lund in 1905, officer exam in 1907, and intendiex. (examination for those intending to become officers) in 1912. He served as a second lieutenant in the Södra skånska infantry regiment from 1907, intend iiaisip. (officer in the intelligence service) in 1910, lieutenant in 1911, second intend. in 1912, intend. in the same year, and regimental intend. in the Västgöta regiment from 1913 to 1926. He became a Captain in 1915 and was on the reserve list from 1926. He worked as a read-court official at Vänersborg since 1926. He was a member of the board of directors for Restad Hospital from 1920, board of directors for the state's institution for mentally disabled girls in Vänersborg from 1922, board of directors for the national divisional office in Vänersborg from 1927 (chairman), and member of the city's finance committee from 1928 to 1934. He was also a member of the board of directors for Kälilshagen Hospital from 1929 and a member of the city council from 1930 to 1934. He was awarded RSO (Knight of the Order of the Sword) and RVO (Knight of the Order of Vasa).
